    notes:
      "## Beginner Protocol\n25mg/day AM × 4–6 weeks. Track: cognitive function (memory, focus, verbal recall), mood, sleep quality, energy. Pregnenolone effects are often subjectively perceptible within 1–2 weeks (faster than DHEA's typical timeline). If positive subjective response, continue; if no response at 6 weeks, increase to 50mg/day or reassess use case.\n\n## Advanced Protocol\nLayer with: DHEA 10–50mg/day (downstream precursor; combinations are common in adrenal/longevity protocols), 7-Keto DHEA 100mg/day (non-androgenic metabolic effects), Lion's Mane 1000mg/day (cognitive synergy via different mechanism — NGF/BDNF), Bacopa Monnieri 300mg/day (cognitive synergy via different mechanism — cholinergic/anti-inflammatory). Comprehensive HPA axis support: ashwagandha + vitamin C + B5 + magnesium + sleep optimization.\n\nFor users with TBI / cognitive concerns: pregnenolone fits in comprehensive cognitive recovery protocols alongside Lion's Mane, omega-3 high-DHA, B-complex (especially methylated B12, methylfolate), creatine 5g/day, and standard cognitive rehabilitation. Marx and colleagues' work on pregnenolone in PTSD and TBI provides emerging evidence base.\n\n## Pregnenolone vs DHEA — Decision Frame\nThese are upstream/downstream in the same biosynthetic pathway:\n- **Pregnenolone:** apex of steroid synthesis; provides substrate for ALL downstream steroids (progesterone, cortisol, DHEA, testosterone, estradiol); has direct neurosteroid effects independent of conversion\n- **DHEA:** branch in the pathway after pregnenolone; converts to androgens and estrogens; less direct brain activity than pregnenolone\n\nFor users prioritizing cognitive/mood effects → pregnenolone is more direct.\nFor users prioritizing adrenal androgen/estrogen support → DHEA is more direct.\nFor comprehensive HRT precursor support → both layered (most common HRT-clinic protocol).\n\n## Cognitive Use Case — The Strongest Evidence\nThe Flood and Roberts work in animal models established pregnenolone as one of the most potent memory enhancers studied — effect sizes substantially exceeding many classical nootropics. Translation to human cognitive enhancement has been more variable but generally positive in studies of older adults with low baseline cognition or cognitive complaints. The neurosteroid framing (direct brain activity) is more evidence-supported than the 'feeds downstream hormones' framing for human cognitive use cases.\n\nFor users seeking cognitive support specifically: pregnenolone 25–50mg/day AM is a reasonable component of cognitive stacks, particularly for users in midlife or older with cognitive complaints. Pairs naturally with Lion's Mane, Bacopa, and other cognitive supplements via different mechanisms.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A for oral/sublingual. Topical compounded cream: applied to inner thigh, inner forearm, or other thin-skin areas; rotate sites; allow absorption before clothing contact. Sublingual troches: hold under tongue 60–90 seconds before swallowing.\n\n## Synergies\n**DHEA:** downstream branch; combinations common. **7-Keto DHEA:** non-androgenic complement. **Lion's Mane:** cognitive synergy via NGF/BDNF mechanism (different from pregnenolone's NMDA modulation). **Bacopa Monnieri:** cognitive synergy via cholinergic/anti-inflammatory mechanism. **Omega-3 high-DHA:** foundational neurosteroid + membrane support combination.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nFlood and Roberts (1980s–1990s, animal models): foundational memory-enhancement studies establishing pregnenolone as one of the most potent memory enhancers studied. Marx 2009 (n=21 schizophrenia, 500mg/day × 8 weeks): improved positive symptoms and cognition. Marx 2014 (PTSD, lower dose protocols): emerging evidence for combat-related PTSD. Vallée 2014 (review of neurosteroid pregnenolone effects): mechanism review. Multiple TBI studies (ongoing): emerging evidence base for cognitive recovery contexts.\n\nHuman pregnenolone trials are less extensive than DHEA trials due to lower commercial visibility despite mechanistic superiority for cognitive use cases.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism well-characterized. Animal model evidence robust for cognitive enhancement. Human RCT evidence growing but less extensive than DHEA's database. The neurosteroid pharmacology is interesting and distinct from simple precursor-hormone framing.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid mechanistic case especially for direct neurosteroid effects; cognitive enhancement evidence robust in animal models, growing in humans; the upstream-precursor function for downstream hormones less clearly established in human supplementation context. Anecdote: widely used in integrative medicine and HRT contexts; cognitive and mood effects often reported within 1–2 weeks; pairs naturally with DHEA. Decision frame: foundational compound for cognitive/mood and adrenal precursor support; pairs naturally with DHEA (downstream branch); reasonable inclusion in comprehensive HRT/cognitive protocols; titrate based on subjective response rather than fixed lab targeting (the lab markers for pregnenolone effects are less standardized than DHEA-S).",
