    mechanism:
      "Naturally occurring metabolite of DHEA produced via 7α-hydroxylation followed by 7β-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase oxidation. The 7-keto position prevents conversion back to DHEA or downstream to androgens (testosterone) and estrogens (estradiol) — this is the central distinguishing feature of 7-Keto DHEA vs regular DHEA. **Mechanism — the non-androgenic, non-estrogenic distinction**: regular DHEA's primary clinical concern is downstream conversion to sex hormones (androgens and estrogens) — beneficial for HRT precursor support contexts but problematic for users with hormone-sensitive cancer history, PCOS women (already-elevated androgens), men wanting effects without aromatization, and athletes facing drug-testing. 7-Keto DHEA's structural modification at the 7-position prevents this downstream conversion, allowing access to some non-hormonal DHEA effects without sex hormone elevation. The 7-keto group is enzymatically introduced and prevents reverse conversion to DHEA and forward conversion through the standard steroidogenic pathway. **Mechanism — thermogenic / metabolic effects**: 7-Keto DHEA's primary commercial positioning is as a thermogenic / fat-loss compound. The proposed mechanism involves activation of thermogenic enzymes (glycerol-3-phosphate dehydrogenase, malic enzyme) leading to modest increases in resting metabolic rate. The thermogenic effect size in published RCTs is modest (~3-4% RMR increase) but consistent. **Mechanism — immune effects**: 7-Keto DHEA enhances some Th1 immune responses similar to regular DHEA but without the androgen/estrogen pathway involvement. **Mechanism — cortisol modulation**: 7-Keto DHEA has anti-glucocorticoid activity in some contexts — opposes some cortisol effects at the cellular level. **Pharmacokinetics**: oral bioavailability moderate (~30%); plasma half-life ~2-3 hours; tissue effects sustained. Less first-pass metabolism than parent DHEA. Single morning dose typically produces 24-hour elevation. **Regulatory status**: OTC supplement in US (DSHEA); not WADA-banned (regular DHEA is WADA-banned for athletes; 7-Keto is not because it doesn't elevate testosterone or other banned androgens). Quality control varies among OTC products — verify third-party testing.",
