    sourcingNotes:
      "OTC supplement in US. Reputable brands: Pure Encapsulations 7-Keto DHEA, Life Extension 7-Keto DHEA, Source Naturals 7-Keto, Jarrow Formulas 7-Keto. Branded ingredient: 7-Keto Naturalean (Humanetics) is the patented form used in many of the published RCTs. Cost: $15-30/month at typical doses.",
    notes:
      "## When to Choose 7-Keto Over Regular DHEA\nThe decision frame is straightforward when the use case is clear:\n\n**Choose 7-Keto when:**\n- Hormone-sensitive cancer history (breast, prostate, ovarian)\n- PCOS women (already-elevated androgens — regular DHEA contraindicated)\n- Athletes subject to WADA testing (regular DHEA is banned)\n- Men wanting metabolic/adrenal effects without aromatization to estradiol\n- Users wanting thermogenic / fat-loss effects (this is 7-Keto's commercial positioning)\n- Adrenal support without sex hormone pathway involvement\n\n**Choose regular DHEA when:**\n- HRT precursor support (the actual point of supplementation is downstream sex hormone production)\n- Postmenopausal symptom management (estrogenic conversion is desired)\n- Women with documented low DHEA-S and androgen deficiency symptoms (low libido, fatigue, mood)\n- Men with documented adrenal insufficiency requiring androgen support\n\n**Layer both when:**\n- Comprehensive HRT protocols where some downstream conversion (regular DHEA) is desired plus additional non-hormonal effects (7-Keto)\n- The combination is common in integrative HRT clinics — typically 10-25mg DHEA + 100mg 7-Keto for women, 25-50mg DHEA + 100mg 7-Keto for men\n\n## Beginner Protocol\n100mg/day AM × 8–12 weeks. Track: energy, body composition (if thermogenic application), subjective adrenal markers (energy, stress resilience), weight. The 100mg dose was used in most published RCTs and is the standard starting and maintenance dose.\n\n## Advanced Protocol\nFor comprehensive HRT context: layer 7-Keto 100mg/day + DHEA dose-titrated-to-DHEA-S labs + Pregnenolone 25-50mg/day + targeted nutritional adrenal support (vitamin C, B5, magnesium) + ashwagandha 600mg/day for HPA axis support + sleep optimization.\n\nFor metabolic/fat-loss context: 7-Keto 100mg BID + caffeine (modest) + green tea extract / EGCG + structured exercise + nutrition optimization + sleep. Caveat: thermogenic supplements have modest effect sizes; the foundation work (nutrition, exercise, sleep, NEAT) drives the bulk of metabolic results.\n\n## 7-Keto Specific Use Cases\n**Hormone-sensitive cancer history with low DHEA-S:** 7-Keto provides some adrenal/metabolic effects without the contraindicated estrogen/androgen conversion. Coordinate with oncologist; this is the primary use case where 7-Keto's distinct mechanism matters most.\n\n**Athletes:** WADA-permitted; useful as part of metabolic/recovery protocols where regular DHEA would produce positive tests.\n\n**PCOS women:** typically have elevated androgens; regular DHEA contraindicated. 7-Keto allows access to adrenal support without making PCOS worse.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A — oral capsule. AM dosing matches endogenous circadian pattern. With food preferred for absorption.\n\n## Synergies\n**Regular DHEA:** complementary effect profile (downstream sex hormone vs non-hormonal pathways) — combinations common in HRT protocols. **Pregnenolone:** upstream precursor; broader steroid pathway support. **Ashwagandha:** HPA axis support, complementary mechanism. **Green tea / EGCG / caffeine:** thermogenic stack components. **Vitamin C / B5 / magnesium:** adrenal cofactor nutritional support.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nKalman 2000 (n=30 overweight adults, 100mg BID × 8 weeks): improved body composition, weight loss vs placebo. Zenk 2002 (n=40, 200mg/day × 8 weeks): improved body composition. Multiple smaller trials on adrenal/metabolic endpoints. The clinical trial database is smaller than for regular DHEA but the published evidence specifically supports the thermogenic / metabolic positioning.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism well-characterized. Animal model evidence supportive. Human RCT evidence smaller than regular DHEA's database but specifically supports the thermogenic / metabolic and non-hormonal positioning. The 'no androgen/estrogen conversion' claim is mechanistically grounded — the 7-keto modification structurally prevents the relevant conversions.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid mechanistic case for non-hormonal positioning; modest evidence for thermogenic effects; less extensive RCT database than regular DHEA. Anecdote: widely used in fitness/metabolic contexts; subjective effects modest but consistent with mechanism; the non-WADA-banned status makes it more accessible for athletes than regular DHEA. Decision frame: useful complement to regular DHEA in comprehensive HRT protocols; primary use case for hormone-sensitive populations or athletes; reasonable thermogenic adjunct (modest effect size relative to lifestyle interventions).",
